SLAVERY AND JEWS Published By Western Front Walter White 

The story of the slaves in America begins with Christopher Columbus. His voyage to America 
was not financed by Queen Isabella but by Luis de Santangelo, who advanced the sum of , ducats 
(about , unds - today equal to , unds) to finance the voyage, which began on August , 
 

Columbus was accompanied by five 'maranos' (Jews who had forsworn their religion and 
supsedly became Catholics), Luis de Tones, erpreter, Marco, the surgeon, Bernal, the physician, 
Alonzo de la Calle and Gabriel Sanchez. (Ref. 'The International Jew' by Henry Ford). 

Gabriel Sanchez, abetted by the other four Jews, sold Columbus on the idea of capturing  
Indians and selling them as slaves in Seville, Spain, which was done. Columbus did not receive any of 
the money from the sale of the slaves but he became the viim of a conspiracy fostered by Bernal, the 
ship's door. He, Columbus, suffered injustice and imprisonment as his reward. ˜Betrayed by the five 
maranos (Jews) whom he had trusted and helped. This, ironically, was the beginning of slavery in the 
Americas. ('Adventures of an African Slaver' by Malcolm Cowley, , p. ) 

The Jews were expelled from Spain on August ,  and from Portugal in . Many of these 
Jews emigrated to Holland, where they set up the Dutch West Indies Company to exoit the new world. 

